Due to significant growth in the physical supply of marine fuel to vessels at sea and in ports in Australasia a new role has been created to enhance the profitability and service delivery of this world wide bunker trader’s Australasian bunker trading activities.  Based from the Singapore office this role will report to the Asia Physical Trading Manager.
ABOUT OUR CLIENT
Our client is a Blue Chip global fuel distribution and logistics company who are involved in the physical distribution of marine fuel.  Globally they own and operate in barges, storage tanks and manage sourcing, blending and transportation of marine fuel via harbour bunkering, high seas bunkering and bunkering on the roads.  They also operate as a reseller and provide risk management solutions to clients.
THE SUCCESSFUL APPLICANT
This role deals with all aspects relating to the daily physical bunker trading activities in the Australasia region.  This role is an integrated part of the Asia Physical team who manage the company’s physical operations in Singapore and Australia.
More specifically the ideal candidate will have experience in:- Bunker trading on the physical desk (minimum of 5 years). Worked in bunker trading or physical bunker operations in Singapore. Daily physical bunker trading, setting prices in the Asia Physical operations environment and monitoring exposure. Optimize procurement and liaise with other points of contact regarding operations and sales. You will have a proven track record of meeting physical trading budgets and ensure the achievement of Asia Physical overall earnings budgets.  Be a College graduate or similar. Your soft skills will include the ability to work in a team, communicate fluently in English and Mandarin, and remain focused when placed under pressure.  You will thrive in a high energy and pressure environment.  You will be able to work in a structured organisation and adapt to the organisational culture. You will demonstrate the ability to work with different people to resolve issues.
JOB DESCRIPTION Day to day physical bunker trading. Setting bunker fuel prices in Asia Physical operations. Monitor exposure regarding physical trades. Optimize the procurement opportunities, competitive prices and act as a support to the Asia Physical Trading Manager. Liaising with operations and sales teams as well as dealing with the Cargo resupply units  in Australia. REMUNERATION PACKAGE
